WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.135 --> 00:00:06.334
<i>Carroll was convicted in 2004 for
the murders of 14 young women.</i>

2
00:00:06.507 --> 00:00:09.841
The warden granted Joe Carroll's
request for a transfer. He's leaving.

3
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:13.412
Joe's not in the transport
vehicle. Where the hell is he?

4
00:00:14.381 --> 00:00:18.341
- So Joe's free. Now I get locked up.
- Protective custody. Better if I don't know.

5
00:00:18.519 --> 00:00:22.650
Hey. Morning. I know you're scared
of me. but I hope that will change.

6
00:00:22.823 --> 00:00:26.658
- My son needs a mother.
- I have an idea how we can find her.

7
00:00:26.827 --> 00:00:30.525
She has to die because
you slept with Joe's wife.

8
00:00:30.697 --> 00:00:33.326
- Why did you do it?
- Because I love her.

9
00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:37.096
Nick Donovan made an encrypted call
checking the status of Claire Matthews.

10
00:00:37.304 --> 00:00:39.034
Your wife is in
Huntingdon County.

11
00:00:40.440 --> 00:00:44.104
- What's taking her so long?
- I looked all over. She and Joey are gone.

12
00:00:45.479 --> 00:00:47.243
Emma. Why did you leave us?

13
00:00:47.414 --> 00:00:50.009
If you don't get him to a
hospital. he's going to die.

14
00:00:50.183 --> 00:00:52.015
You can do this.

15
00:00:52.219 --> 00:00:53.278
I'm sorry.

16
00:00:53.453 --> 00:00:55.388
I received a very
exciting e-mail.

17
00:00:55.556 --> 00:00:59.220
I wanted to tell you about it.
but I thought I'd surprise you.

18
00:01:18.545 --> 00:01:20.639
Man. you're a heavy sleeper.

19
00:01:23.216 --> 00:01:26.846
Get up. You don't wanna
sleep the day away.

20
00:01:30.157 --> 00:01:31.318
What are you doing here?

21
00:01:31.491 --> 00:01:35.428
I'm trying to get you up. Now.
go. come on. get in the shower.

22
00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:38.899
Heh. you're gonna
miss breakfast.

23
00:02:21.708 --> 00:02:22.734
<i>And now...</i>

24
00:02:23.010 --> 00:02:24.387
<i>an update from
Richmond. Virginia.</i>

25
00:02:24.411 --> 00:02:27.108
<i>A press conference has not
eased our nation's paranoia...</i>

26
00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:29.715
<i>as we've learned that
FBI. CIA and NSA...</i>

27
00:02:29.916 --> 00:02:33.353
<i>are now all in pursuit of Joe
Carroll and his cult of serial killers.</i>

28
00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:35.716
Amanda Porter's
not exactly talking.

29
00:02:35.922 --> 00:02:39.324
No. I take that back.
She's actually saying a lot.

30
00:02:39.860 --> 00:02:43.297
- And what is she saying? PARKER:
Well. let's see. Uh. she's a Pisces.

31
00:02:43.463 --> 00:02:46.900
Favorite movie is <i>The Notebook.</i>
She's an advocate for the death penalty.

32
00:02:47.067 --> 00:02:51.471
She believes in creationism over
evolution. enjoys '70s soft rock...

33
00:02:51.638 --> 00:02:54.369
and hates peanut butter.
whole milk and Anne Hathaway.

34
00:02:54.541 --> 00:02:57.739
- They gotta let me talk to her.
- I agree. But it's D.C.'s show now.

35
00:02:57.944 --> 00:02:59.469
I mean. it's their call.

36
00:03:00.013 --> 00:03:02.482
Hey. you gotta let me
talk to Amanda Porter.

37
00:03:02.649 --> 00:03:05.642
- It's not going to happen. Ryan.
- Come on. This woman knows me.

38
00:03:05.819 --> 00:03:08.311
- I broke her once.
- He's right. he should be there.

39
00:03:08.488 --> 00:03:11.219
Ah. if D.C. guys can't break
her. I'll recommend it. okay?

40
00:03:12.025 --> 00:03:13.254
We got another problem.

41
00:03:13.460 --> 00:03:16.487
- Quantico found a break in their server.
- We were hacked?

42
00:03:16.663 --> 00:03:18.427
Where was their fail-safe?
- Stalled.

43
00:03:18.598 --> 00:03:20.276
Lines were interrupted
for several seconds.

44
00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:22.428
A worm encrypted with a virus.

45
00:03:22.602 --> 00:03:24.867
- What did they access?
- Telecommunications log.

46
00:03:25.038 --> 00:03:28.167
Calls to Protective Custody. It's
possible Joe made an attempt...

47
00:03:28.341 --> 00:03:30.867
to trace Claire Matthews
via our satellite system.

48
00:03:31.044 --> 00:03:32.672
We gotta move her. - Yes. we do.

49
00:03:32.846 --> 00:03:35.748
Ah. but we need you to convince
her of that. Will you call her?

50
00:03:36.750 --> 00:03:40.744
Using what phone exactly?
No. I'm gonna do it in person.

51
00:03:40.921 --> 00:03:43.789
Get me a chopper. I wanna
be in charge of her safety detail.

52
00:03:43.990 --> 00:03:45.356
- Like hell.
- Let him go.

53
00:03:45.525 --> 00:03:47.790
- He's not an agent. Debra.
- It's not negotiable.

54
00:03:50.363 --> 00:03:54.198
The cell tower linked to your wife is
near a roadside motel on Highway 31.

55
00:03:54.367 --> 00:03:57.735
Typically. there's five to
six agents per safe house...

56
00:03:57.904 --> 00:03:59.896
in a designated area
away from guests.

57
00:04:00.073 --> 00:04:04.010
I'm thinking an M17 or my
Micro Uzi with a silencer.

58
00:04:05.545 --> 00:04:08.640
- You ex-military?
- Hell. no. We're better than that.

59
00:04:09.149 --> 00:04:12.711
- They were both raised by militia.
- Well. constitutional extremists...

60
00:04:13.587 --> 00:04:15.453
to be accurate.

61
00:04:17.591 --> 00:04:20.527
- You sure about this?
- You want your wife back.

62
00:04:20.694 --> 00:04:24.654
These two can do it. They've
got the skills and the know-how.

63
00:04:27.667 --> 00:04:29.966
You go with them. Roderick.

64
00:04:30.804 --> 00:04:35.105
I can't. I gotta work
today. Duty calls.

65
00:04:35.275 --> 00:04:37.608
Oh. I'm sure you'll work it out.

66
00:04:37.778 --> 00:04:39.747
Heh. I'm sure I can't.

67
00:04:41.681 --> 00:04:45.846
I insist. Roderick.
You've failed twice.

68
00:04:46.052 --> 00:04:48.248
This time. I want my wife.

69
00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:05.367
- Jacob!
- Hey. squirt.

70
00:05:09.042 --> 00:05:12.376
- How you doing?
- Look. Jacob's here.

71
00:05:13.013 --> 00:05:16.177
- Hey. Jacob.
- When did you get here? Where's Paul?

72
00:05:16.349 --> 00:05:20.946
I got here late last
night. And Paul. well...

73
00:05:21.121 --> 00:05:22.680
Paul couldn't make it.

74
00:05:22.856 --> 00:05:25.519
Hey. Joey. will you give
Jacob and me a minute?

75
00:05:27.194 --> 00:05:31.825
- It's okay. dude. We don't need a minute.
- Jacob. let me explain. Let me talk to you.

76
00:05:35.001 --> 00:05:37.903
Look at this place. Will you
show me around. buddy?

77
00:05:38.104 --> 00:05:39.629
- Will you do that?
- Sure.

78
00:05:39.806 --> 00:05:41.399
Let's go.

79
00:06:01.261 --> 00:06:03.821
When is Ryan Hardy getting here?

80
00:06:07.534 --> 00:06:10.629
Okay. Good. He's pulling up now.

81
00:06:11.171 --> 00:06:12.764
All right. Thanks.

82
00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:36.295
Ryan Hardy? Marshal Ferguson.

83
00:06:36.463 --> 00:06:38.091
Claire's in the next room.

84
00:06:41.768 --> 00:06:43.396
Hey. CLAIRE: Hey.

85
00:06:50.510 --> 00:06:52.672
Ah. nobody's
telling me the truth.

86
00:06:54.247 --> 00:06:56.546
What do you wanna
know? I'll tell you anything.

87
00:06:56.716 --> 00:07:01.416
Uh. for starters. why was
I denied media access?

88
00:07:02.122 --> 00:07:05.058
Joe's people were targeting
women named Claire Matthews...

89
00:07:05.225 --> 00:07:07.387
in the Richmond area and...

90
00:07:07.560 --> 00:07:09.620
two of them were killed.

91
00:07:09.796 --> 00:07:12.322
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

92
00:07:12.499 --> 00:07:15.333
I just... I don't understand
why no one can find him.

93
00:07:15.502 --> 00:07:17.937
How does a cult of killers
stay hidden this long?

94
00:07:18.104 --> 00:07:21.097
His followers have
proven to be sophisticated.

95
00:07:21.274 --> 00:07:24.642
Their tactical skills. cyber
invasion. they're on a terrorist level.

96
00:07:24.811 --> 00:07:28.145
Plus. some of them
are trained military.

97
00:07:28.315 --> 00:07:30.511
And now he's with Joey.

98
00:07:30.717 --> 00:07:33.118
That madman has my son.

99
00:07:34.020 --> 00:07:36.455
We need to move
you someplace safer.

100
00:07:45.365 --> 00:07:47.527
Those are cool shades.
Where'd you get those?

101
00:07:53.807 --> 00:07:57.327
Be advised. looks like they're headed for
the stairway or the elevator at this time.

102
00:08:13.893 --> 00:08:16.021
Whole wing is locked down.

103
00:08:16.196 --> 00:08:18.859
They're somewhere in this
hallway. I got the master key.

104
00:08:19.032 --> 00:08:21.160
See you on the other side.

105
00:08:27.707 --> 00:08:30.768
Do a walk-through. Let
me know when it's clear.

106
00:08:30.977 --> 00:08:32.001
Yes. sir. You got it.

107
00:08:33.146 --> 00:08:35.638
- Where's Claire?
- Right here. I'm ready.

108
00:08:36.816 --> 00:08:38.978
Hey. is there a
problem out there?

109
00:08:39.152 --> 00:08:42.680
My men in the lobby saw a
couple guys who looked suspicious.

110
00:08:50.597 --> 00:08:53.157
Ah. let's do this.

111
00:08:57.203 --> 00:08:58.762
No screw-ups.

112
00:09:22.829 --> 00:09:24.821
Clear.

113
00:09:30.603 --> 00:09:32.403
You and Claire go out
back. I got you covered.

114
00:09:32.572 --> 00:09:33.972
Stay with me.

115
00:09:36.576 --> 00:09:37.908
Okay. come on.

116
00:09:38.945 --> 00:09:40.538
Clear.

117
00:09:58.098 --> 00:09:59.122
Come on.

118
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.134
Get in.

119
00:10:13.947 --> 00:10:15.176
- Come here.
- Wait.

120
00:10:16.382 --> 00:10:19.580
- Back off. Drop the gun.
- Or what?

121
00:10:19.752 --> 00:10:21.880
You're not gonna shoot her.

122
00:10:27.026 --> 00:10:29.427
Okay. come on. Come
on. we gotta go. Come on.

123
00:10:32.999 --> 00:10:34.900
Damn. that hurt.

124
00:10:56.990 --> 00:10:58.856
- You have a cell phone?
- No.

125
00:10:59.025 --> 00:11:01.051
Take out the SIM card.

126
00:11:04.831 --> 00:11:06.493
Where are we going?

127
00:11:11.738 --> 00:11:13.536
Someplace safe.

128
00:11:22.448 --> 00:11:25.179
I don't understand. Where is he?
- I don't know.

129
00:11:25.351 --> 00:11:28.913
He destroyed his SIM card and
deactivated the GPS on his car.

130
00:11:29.088 --> 00:11:31.751
He's being smart. He's
worried about being traced.

131
00:11:31.958 --> 00:11:33.722
So he must have Claire.

132
00:11:33.893 --> 00:11:36.863
- Where would they go?
- Brooklyn. It's a four-hour drive.

133
00:11:37.030 --> 00:11:39.329
Have an undercover
patrol his place in Brooklyn.

134
00:11:39.499 --> 00:11:42.196
- You think he went home?
- FBI surveillance footage is in.

135
00:11:42.368 --> 00:11:45.236
There's four dead at the scene.
including Marshal Ferguson.

136
00:11:45.405 --> 00:11:48.273
- I have face recognition.
- Let's get IDs.

137
00:11:48.474 --> 00:11:50.773
We need to find them
before they find Hardy.

138
00:12:11.631 --> 00:12:14.499
- Is this the place?
- I hope so.

139
00:12:15.134 --> 00:12:17.069
I'm looking for a
guy named Tyson.

140
00:12:19.038 --> 00:12:21.633
- What the hell are you doing here?
- Heh.

141
00:12:21.808 --> 00:12:23.071
Come here.

142
00:12:25.345 --> 00:12:27.314
Heh. this is Claire. - Hey.

143
00:12:27.513 --> 00:12:29.641
- Claire.
- Good to meet you.

144
00:12:29.816 --> 00:12:32.718
Yeah. Come on. let's go inside.

145
00:12:37.056 --> 00:12:38.991
So how do you two
know each other?

146
00:12:39.158 --> 00:12:40.878
Uh. we went through
Quantico together.

147
00:12:40.927 --> 00:12:44.295
I've been stuck with him ever
since. Tried to get rid of him.

148
00:12:44.464 --> 00:12:47.832
I dumped him on the road a couple
of times. but he found his way back.

149
00:12:48.034 --> 00:12:50.663
- Are you still with the Bureau?
- I'm no longer an agent.

150
00:12:50.837 --> 00:12:54.774
In fact. I'm no longer alive.
thanks to a certain crime syndicate.

151
00:12:55.475 --> 00:12:57.808
I now live in the wonderful
land of nonexistence.

152
00:12:57.977 --> 00:13:00.105
Tyson's been in witness
protection for four years.

153
00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:01.373
Oh.

154
00:13:01.981 --> 00:13:06.009
So you did the right thing
coming here. This is a safe place.

155
00:13:06.185 --> 00:13:07.813
Hey.

156
00:13:07.987 --> 00:13:10.650
Talk to me. Who's
trying to kill you?

157
00:13:10.823 --> 00:13:15.488
Three of Joe's followers took
out a motel full of federal agents.

158
00:13:15.662 --> 00:13:17.187
But we lost them.

159
00:13:17.830 --> 00:13:20.197
No one's gonna find you here.

160
00:13:21.801 --> 00:13:23.360
Thanks. Ty.

161
00:13:23.569 --> 00:13:25.470
Hey. that's what
friends are for.

162
00:13:34.514 --> 00:13:36.881
Okay. I've read enough.

163
00:13:37.817 --> 00:13:39.308
You shouldn't do this.

164
00:13:40.019 --> 00:13:44.013
This will make you rich and famous for five
minutes. and then it's gonna be a bad idea.

165
00:13:44.190 --> 00:13:47.683
- Pfft. tell me why.
- This is gonna define you.

166
00:13:47.860 --> 00:13:51.456
Ry. you are a kick-ass
agent. but if you publish this...

167
00:13:51.631 --> 00:13:55.693
you're gonna be that one agent. the
Joe Carroll guy. forever and always.

168
00:13:55.868 --> 00:13:57.996
What if I told you
I wanted to do it?

169
00:13:58.805 --> 00:14:02.572
That it might help me?

170
00:14:02.742 --> 00:14:04.734
You know. really help me.

171
00:14:07.246 --> 00:14:09.681
Then I say go for
it. What do I know?

172
00:14:15.588 --> 00:14:17.580
I miss you. man.

173
00:14:17.757 --> 00:14:20.022
It's really good to see you.

174
00:14:25.765 --> 00:14:26.789
Wow.

175
00:14:26.966 --> 00:14:28.901
This is a cool room.

176
00:14:29.068 --> 00:14:30.559
I guess. Whatever.

177
00:14:30.737 --> 00:14:33.707
Hey. this place is awesome.
What. you don't like it here?

178
00:14:33.873 --> 00:14:36.342
I don't know. I miss my mom.

179
00:14:37.276 --> 00:14:39.040
Jacob.

180
00:14:39.212 --> 00:14:40.271
How did you sleep?

181
00:14:41.180 --> 00:14:44.548
- Morning. Joe. I slept great.
- Good.

182
00:14:44.751 --> 00:14:46.151
Good morning. Joey.

183
00:14:46.786 --> 00:14:49.847
- Hey. Joey. don't be rude.
- No. no. no. It's all right.

184
00:14:50.523 --> 00:14:54.255
My son is still. uh. adjusting.

185
00:14:56.596 --> 00:14:58.895
Did you get a chance to
have a good look around?

186
00:14:59.065 --> 00:15:01.125
- Yeah. Joey gave me the grand tour.
- Good.

187
00:15:01.300 --> 00:15:04.099
I'm sure you're gonna be
very happy here with us all.

188
00:15:05.938 --> 00:15:10.672
There's just one thing
I'd like you to do for me.

189
00:15:11.177 --> 00:15:13.043
Yeah. sure. Anything.

190
00:15:13.212 --> 00:15:14.771
You talk to Emma.

191
00:15:15.882 --> 00:15:18.579
Give her a chance to
explain her side of things.

192
00:15:18.751 --> 00:15:21.152
- You two need each other.
- After what she did...

193
00:15:21.320 --> 00:15:23.755
She was taking care of my son.

194
00:15:24.557 --> 00:15:26.549
She did what was asked of her.

195
00:15:26.726 --> 00:15:29.127
And now I ask a favor of you.

196
00:15:29.295 --> 00:15:32.265
Resolve this. Settle
your differences.

197
00:15:33.065 --> 00:15:34.897
You understand?

198
00:15:36.402 --> 00:15:41.238
- She left us for dead.
- I'm sure that's how you feel.

199
00:15:41.407 --> 00:15:44.241
But I need you to forgive her.

200
00:15:45.645 --> 00:15:48.774
You love Emma. I know you do.

201
00:15:49.382 --> 00:15:50.406
Okay?

202
00:15:56.956 --> 00:16:00.085
Emma's a selfish
bitch. Always was.

203
00:16:19.512 --> 00:16:22.914
Surveillance footage from the
hotel matched Vincent McKinnley.

204
00:16:23.082 --> 00:16:25.642
Wanted in connection with
three murders in New York.

205
00:16:25.818 --> 00:16:28.287
- The other's Brock Wickford.
- Brothers. in a sense.

206
00:16:28.454 --> 00:16:31.117
They met in the juvenile
system. Both products of abuse.

207
00:16:31.290 --> 00:16:34.818
They were sent to a foster home
that was busted for militia activity.

208
00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:38.761
- I'm sure they picked up great skills there.
- I hacked into Vincent's e-mail.

209
00:16:38.931 --> 00:16:41.696
He communicates internationally.
same as our other cult folks.

210
00:16:41.868 --> 00:16:43.564
I couldn't retrieve
any content...

211
00:16:43.736 --> 00:16:45.976
but I did find this one sequence
embedded in his e-mails.

212
00:16:47.106 --> 00:16:48.404
What is that? A password?

213
00:16:48.574 --> 00:16:50.668
It could be. It's
meant to be hidden.

214
00:16:50.843 --> 00:16:53.813
Ah. Charles Mead had a
series of encrypted URLs.

215
00:16:54.146 --> 00:16:55.239
See if you get lucky.

216
00:16:56.716 --> 00:16:58.048
Yeah?

217
00:16:58.985 --> 00:17:00.647
Nothing? Ah.

218
00:17:00.820 --> 00:17:02.311
Thank you.

219
00:17:02.855 --> 00:17:07.122
Ryan and Claire aren't at his place.
They've just completely disappeared.

220
00:17:17.970 --> 00:17:19.529
Hi.

221
00:17:22.074 --> 00:17:25.340
Joe wanted me to come
and talk to you. so here I am.

222
00:17:27.146 --> 00:17:28.478
Can you sit?

223
00:17:42.728 --> 00:17:44.287
Well?

224
00:17:44.931 --> 00:17:46.263
Okay.

225
00:17:49.902 --> 00:17:50.961
This is hard.

226
00:17:52.605 --> 00:17:55.939
I've been thinking about what
to say to you since last night.

227
00:17:56.108 --> 00:17:58.600
When you were
surprised to see me?

228
00:18:02.515 --> 00:18:05.542
- Did you think I was dead?
- No.

229
00:18:05.718 --> 00:18:07.880
I don't know. I didn't
know what to think.

230
00:18:11.591 --> 00:18:16.029
I'm so sorry about Paul.

231
00:18:16.862 --> 00:18:19.388
- I loved him too.
- Pfft. no. you didn't.

232
00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:21.624
I did.

233
00:18:24.370 --> 00:18:27.772
I know you think
I abandoned you.

234
00:18:27.940 --> 00:18:30.102
And maybe I did. but
you can't just blame me.

235
00:18:30.276 --> 00:18:34.611
- I was doing what Roderick told me to do.
- You didn't have to leave us.

236
00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:37.750
It was crazy that
night. Confusing.

237
00:18:37.917 --> 00:18:41.752
- I was nearly killed too. I almost lost Joey.
- No. you didn't.

238
00:18:41.921 --> 00:18:44.755
